With a sharp, decisive motion, Arthur brought the silver flask down upon the desk's edge. It shattered with a muffled crack, sending splinters of metal and a plume of dark liquid across the polished mahogany. The bitter, almond-like scent intensified, mingling with the rain-heavy air as the last vestiges of its deadly contents seeped into the wood grain, leaving a dark, damp stain and a scattering of gleaming fragments. The study now smelled distinctly of spilled poison, its secrets irrevocably scattered. What further damning details did this room conceal?

